quran[58]{c,v,t}:
  75,1,Nay! I swear by (or call to witness) the Day of Resurrection
  75,2,Nay! I swear by (or call to witness) the self-accusing soul
  75,3,Does man think that We shall not gather his bones
  75,4,Yea! We are able to make complete his very fingertips
  75,5,Nay! Man desires to give the lie to what is before him
  75,6,"He asks, \"When is the day of resurrection"
  75,7,So when the sight becomes dazzled
  75,8,And the moon becomes dark
  75,9,And the sun and the moon are brought together
  75,10,"Man shall say on that day, \"Whither can I flee for refuge"
  75,11,By no means! There shall be no place of refuge
  75,12,With your Lord alone shall on that day be the place of rest
  75,13,Man shall on that day be informed of what he sent before and what he put off
  75,14,Nay! Man is telling evidence against himself
  75,15,Though he puts forth his excuses
  75,16,Move not your tongue with it (the Quran) to make haste with it
  75,17,Surely it is for Us to collect it and to recite (or enact) it
  75,18,"Therefore when We have recited it, follow its recitation"
  75,19,"Nay, more, it is for Us to explain (and clarify) it"
  75,20,Nay! But you do love the fleeting Now
  75,21,And neglect the Hereafter
  75,22,Some faces on that Day shall be bright
  75,23,Looking to their Lord
  75,24,And other faces on that Day shall be gloomy
  75,25,Knowing that there will be made to befall them some great calamity
  75,26,Nay! When the soul comes up to the throat
  75,27,"And it is said, \"Who will be a magician (to restore him)"
  75,28,And he is sure that it is the time of parting
  75,29,And one leg will be tied to another (i.e. after death)
  75,30,To your Lord on that day shall be the driving
  75,31,"So he did not accept the truth, nor did he pray"
  75,32,But called the truth a lie and turned back
  75,33,"Then he went to his folk, arrogant"
  75,34,Nearer unto you and nearer (comes the doom)
  75,35,"Again, nearer unto you and nearer (comes the doom)"
  75,36,Does man think that he is to be left to wander aimless (or purposeless)
  75,37,Was he not a small seed in the seminal elements
  75,38,"Then he was a clot of blood, so He created (him) then made (him) perfect"
  75,39,"Then He made of him two kinds, the male and the female"
  75,40,Is not He able to give life to the dead
  76,1,"Was there not over man a long period of time when he was a thing unremembered (nothing, not worth mention)"
  76,2,"Surely We have created man from a small mingled life-germ; in order to try him, We made him hearing and seeing"
  76,3,"Surely We have shown him the way: he may be thankful or unthankful"
  76,4,Surely We have prepared for the unbelievers chains and yokes and a burning fire
  76,5,Surely the righteous shall drink of a cup the admixture of which is camphor
  76,6,"A fountain from which the servants of Allah shall drink, flows with abundance"
  76,7,Because they fulfil their vows and fear a day the evil of which spreads far and wide
  76,8,And they give food out of love for Allah to the poor and the orphan and the captive
  76,9,(Saying) We only feed you for Allah´s sake; we desire from you neither reward nor thanks
  76,10,"Surely we fear from our Lord a stern, distressful day"
  76,11,Therefore Allah will deliver them from the evil of that day and will shed on them the Light of Beauty and Joy
  76,12,"And reward them, because they were patient, with a Garden and garments of silk"
  76,13,"Reclining therein on raised couches, they shall find therein neither the severe heat of the sun nor intense cold"
  76,14,"And shade thereof is close upon them, and clustered fruits thereof bow down"
  76,15,And amongst them shall be passed vessels of silver and goblets of crystal
  76,16,(Transparent as) glass but made of silver; they will determine the measure thereof
  76,17,And they will be given to drink therein a cup whereof the mixture is of Zanjabil
  76,18,From a fountain therein named Salsabil